		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Martingale (probability theory)</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">For the 'martingale betting strategy', see <a href="/wiki/Martingale_(betting_system)" title="Martingale (betting system)">martingale (betting system)</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:342px;"><a href="/wiki/File:HittingTimes1.png" class="image" title="A stopped Brownian motion as an example for a martingale"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/HittingTimes1.png/340px-HittingTimes1.png" width="340" height="255" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:HittingTimes1.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
A stopped <a href="/wiki/Brownian_motion" title="Brownian motion">Brownian motion</a> as an example for a martingale</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>In <a href="/wiki/Probability_theory" title="Probability theory">probability theory</a>, a <b>martingale</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Stochastic_process" title="Stochastic process">stochastic process</a> (i.e., a <a href="/wiki/Sequence" title="Sequence">sequence</a> of <a href="/wiki/Random_variable" title="Random variable">random variables</a>) such that the <a href="/wiki/Conditional_expected_value" title="Conditional expected value" class="mw-redirect">conditional expected value</a> of an observation at some time <i>t</i>, given all the observations up to some earlier time <i>s</i>, is equal to the observation at that earlier time <i>s</i>. Precise <a href="#Definitions" title="">definitions</a> are given below.</p>
